recover_classical_limit.py
consistency_checks/recover_classical_limit.py
Critical Quantum Gravity Validation .py
Comprehensive classical limit verification framework for quantum gravity models. Systematically tests that quantum corrections vanish as 0 by analyzing curvature invariants, waveform amplitudes, and correlation functions. Implements power-law scaling analysis and comparison with classical GR solutions to validate quantum gravity theories recover proper classical behavior.
Repository: warp-sensitivity-analysis
Modified: 2025-05-30
Size: 19,186 bytes
Last Assessment: 2025-07-14
Dependencies:
analyze_sensitivity.pygenerate_2d_blackhole.pyminisuperspace_cosmo.pynumpyscipyndjson
References:
curvature_analysisplanck_scale_analysisenergy_evolutionclassical_gr_solutionsquantum_parameter_scaling

Assessment Notes

484-line quantum gravity classical limit verification system with sophisticated scaling analysis. Key features: (1) Progressive scaling with configurable factors, (2) Multi-observable extraction (Ricci scalar, Kretschmann invariant, waveform RMS), (3) Power-law fitting for quantum correction scaling, (4) Classical GR reference comparison with tolerance checking, (5) Comprehensive logging and error handling. Uses subprocess execution for scaled analysis runs. Critical for validating quantum gravity models maintain physical consistency in classical limit. Well-structured with clear separation between scaling generation, observable extraction, fitting analysis, and reference comparison phases.
